June 15 at 12:00 PM 路

ATTN: Middle School/ High School Parents

Those who currently have school issued Chromebooks, please review the Collection Return Procedure below. We will be collecting the devices on the dates and times listed below. Extended school year (ESY) students should also return their device and will be issued a new device at a later date.

Date/Time: Wednesday 12PM - 8PM

Thursday:

post_text:
Locker Clean Out Update:

The high school will not be having a traditional locker clean out this year. Students will retain the same locker for the 2020-2021 school year. Clearview Staff will retrieve any school issued items from lockers and return them to teachers.
We ask that students return any school issued items (textbooks, novels, library books, sports equipment) that they have at home on Wednesday between 12pm-8pm or Thursday between 8am-4pm.
If you have an emergency and need something from your locker prior to September, please fill out the form below and we will do our best to get that item for you. We hope everyone is safe and healthy.

https://forms.gle/9Tf8aJnU3ZhyJmSn6

post_text:
Last night, To honor our staff, students & especially the 2020 senior class, we joined schools across the nation in the #BeTheLight campaign. At 8:20 (20:20 military time) we left our stadium lights on for 20 minutes in the hour. We miss all of our students and staff and look forward to when we are all able to be together again. Stay safe and healthy! Pioneer Strong!

Thank you to the Pioneer, Mr. Brook, Mr Wolk, Mr Mozzachio & Mr Vicente for their efforts in making this possible!

post_text: Our Robotics and Anatomy students had the opportunity to learn from Dr. Mohammad Abedin-Nasab, an Assistant Professor and the Director of Surgical Robotics Lab at Rowan University. Dr Abedin specializes in surgical robotics, robotics, bio-mechanics, and nonlinear modeling. Our students also had an amazing opportunity to use Haptic devices, which are often used in the medical industry.

The Clearview Middle School Instrumental Music Department would like to congratulate the following students who successfully auditioned for and are now members in the 2020 All-South Jersey Junior High School Honors Band. These students competed with over 300 other students from the South Jersey area. They will all be performing with the All South Jersey Band in March.

Eleanor Race successfully auditioned and made the band on 3 different instruments, Snare drum, mallets and timpani

Ricky Beckman successfully auditioned and made the band on the French Horn

Joey Lindenbaum successfully auditioned and made the band on the Clarinet

Please congratulate these students for this tremendous accomplishment!

post_text: The Clearview Regional High School District was named to the 2019 National Association for Music Merchants (NAMM) Best Communities for Music Education (BCME). This marks the second consecutive year that the Clearview Regional High School District has received this prestigious honor. Now in its 20th year, the Best Communities for Music Education designation is awarded to districts that demonstrate outstanding achievement in efforts to provide music access and education to all students. Inclusion on the BCMS list acknowledges the Clearview Regional School District as one of the top four percent (4%) of school districts for music education in the United States.

On Wednesday March 6th, the Clearview Regional High School Wind Ensemble traveled to Rowan University for the 2019 Region III South Jersey Band Festival. The Wind Ensemble received a Gold Rating from the two adjudicators, finishing with the highest overall score in Region III - Southern New Jersey. This result qualifies the Wind Ensemble to perform at the New Jersey State Band Gala in May, an honor bestowed on just twelve ensembles in the entire state. 2019 marks the third consecutive year in the NJ State Gala for the Clearview Wind Ensemble, and the fifteenth overall since 2000.

We are so proud of the Wind Ensemble and all of their wonderful accomplishments. Congratulations!

Were so proud to share that Clearview High School won first place in the Jefferson Awards Students in Action competition at the Ambassador level (top level for high schools) and Clearview Middle School won second place among the middle school tier! The leaders of the high school competition team are Sonja Hegel, Rebekah Strauss, Paige Bathurst, and NaSiya Taylor.

The Jefferson Awards was started by Jacqueline Kennedy Onassis, Senator Robert Taft Jr., and Sam Beard in 1972 to recognize and celebrate individuals committed to Public service. Later, they created Students in Action to specifically recognize students committed to service.

These awards are whole school awards. Wed like to thank every advisor, club, coach, team, and individual student who has been involved in any service this past yearbecause we are a district that prioritizes service, we continue to receive these honors!

Here's some exciting news from Athletics:

1. The Boys Tennis Team beat Timber Creek 4-1 in the 1st rd of the South, Gr III Tournament. The Team now travels to Mainland today for a 3 PM match.

2. The Girls Lax Team defeated Wash Twp 13-11, capturing their 4th consecutive Gloucester County Lax Cup Championship.

3. Julia Rothstein was recognized as a Scholar Athlete by the South Jersey Coaches Association. She was also selected to speak to the entire group. She did GREAT!!

We are extremely proud of Julia and our Teams and wish them continued success! GO VIEW!!!

post_text: On April 24th, Sean White performed with the West Chester University High School Honors Percussion Ensemble. Sean auditioned before the Assistant Chair of Percussion at WCU last November to gain acceptance into the group, comprised of only 8 students from 7 different school districts across PA and NJ. Sean was the sole representative of NJ and Clearview! He rehearsed with the ensemble at WCU every Sunday from mid-January until April 24th, practicing every day after school as well. Congratulations Sean and thank you for representing Clearview and making us proud!

post_text: Congratulations to our Robotics teams that traveled to North Burlington on Saturday to compete in the Southern New Jersey League Tournament. The teams performed phenomenally with both teams bringing home trophies for being in the finals. In addition, team 12441, Gearview, won the Think Award for their documentation in their engineering notebook. Team 9848, the Mechanical Pioneers, won the Inspire award, the highest award of the event, qualifying them for the NJ STATE CHAMPIONSHIP on February 25th! CONGRATULATIONS and BEST OF LUCK at the championship!

post_text:
We are EXTREMELY excited to say that one of our own has made it BIG TIME! Mike, The Voice, Wolk has taken his high level of enthusiasm and energy to new levels! For those of you who don't know, Mr. Wolk is our announcer for many of our Home Boys' and Girls' basketball games. Well, last night, a portion of his pre-game introduction from this past Saturday's Boys' basketball game appeared on ESPN's Sports Center.

https://www.instagram.com/p/Be1_OgKl9o-/

Needless to say, we are very proud of Mr. Wolk and appreciate the level of excitement he brings to our games!! Don't worry, he has been signed to a long-term contract with Clearview, with a no-trade clause!

GO VIEW!!!
